### Start RxDB Server Replication

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/replication-server.md

Initiates server replication by connecting to a specified endpoint URL. It requires a collection, a replication identifier, the endpoint URL, and optionally headers, push/pull configurations, and live mode. The `replicateServer` function returns a replication state object.

```typescript
import { replicateServer } from 'rxdb-server/plugins/replication-server';

const replicationState = await replicateServer({
    collection: usersCollection,
    replicationIdentifier: 'my-server-replication',
    url: 'http://localhost:80/users/0', // endpoint url with the servers collection schema version at the end
    headers: {
        Authorization: 'Bearer S0VLU0UhI...'
    },
    push: {},
    pull: {},
    live: true
});
```

